    "Commentary Vol. 83": "And Esau `[char_Esau_Gen_25]` seeing that the daughters of Canaan pleased not Isaac his father.] Who he perceived was displeased with the daughters of Canaan, or that they were \u201cevil in [his] eyes\u201d f1448, offensive to him, and disapproved of by him, because of their ill manners: Rebekah is not mentioned, whose displeasure he cared not for.\nVer.\n8. It is the model of our faith today. (Rom. 4:23-25) and the model of our walk and work (Rom. 4:12).\n8. What is the meaning of &quot;The Word of God&quot; which came to Abram?\n8. What two elements of the enlargement of God's announcement to Abraham `[char_Abraham_Exo_17]`?"
